          <msContents>
            <summary>Manuscript is a compendium or manual for use by Hindus wishing to give different kinds of gifts (dāna) and quotes passages from various purāṇic works, especially the Skandapurāṇa, but also selections from the Liṅgapurāṇa, Bhaviṣyapurāṇa, Matsyapurāṇa, and Kūrmapurāṇa, as well as a selection from the Mahābhārata. The manuscript gives the rules (religious law) governing such gifts as the gift of a wife, "gifts" to the recently deceased, gift of a cow, and other gifts. Text also includes a section on mantras for use in worship (pūjā).</summary>
            <textLang>In Sanskrit</textLang>
            <msItem>
              <title>Dānavidhi</title>
              <colophon>Colophon: iti strīyadāsīdānaṃ // (f. 16v).</colophon>
            </msItem>
